{"id":321198,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buzen_Province","text":"was an old province of Japan in the area of Fukuoka Prefecture and \u014Cita Prefecture on the island of Ky\u016Bsh\u016B. Along with Bungo Province, it was sometimes called.\nBuzen had borders with Bungo and Chikuzen Provinces.\nThe ancient capital city of the province was near Toyotsu, Fukuoka.\nHistory.\nIn the Meiji period, the provinces of Japan were converted into prefectures. Maps of Japan and Buzen Province were reformed in the 1870s.\nShrines and Temples.\n\"Usa-jinj\u016B\" was the chief Shinto shrine (\"ichinomiya\") of Buzen.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"List_of_Provinces_of_Japan","surface_form":"old province","offset":7},{"uri":"Japan","surface_form":"Japan","offset":23},{"uri":"Fukuoka_Prefecture","surface_form":"Fukuoka Prefecture","offset":44},{"uri":"%C5%8Cita_Prefecture","surface_form":"\u014Cita Prefecture","offset":67},{"uri":"Ky%C5%ABsh%C5%AB","surface_form":"Ky\u016Bsh\u016B","offset":100},{"uri":"Bungo_Province","surface_form":"Bungo Province","offset":119},{"uri":"Border","surface_form":"border","offset":170},{"uri":"Bungo_Province","surface_form":"Bungo","offset":183},{"uri":"Chikuzen_Province","surface_form":"Chikuzen","offset":193},{"uri":"Capital_(city)","surface_form":"capital city","offset":225},{"uri":"Toyotsu%2C_Fukuoka","surface_form":"Toyotsu, Fukuoka","offset":263},{"uri":"Meiji_period","surface_form":"Meiji period","offset":297},{"uri":"Reform","surface_form":"reform","offset":405},{"uri":"Usa-jinj%C5%AB","surface_form":"Usa-jinj\u016B","offset":450},{"uri":"Shinto_shrine","surface_form":"Shinto shrine","offset":475},{"uri":"Ichinomiya","surface_form":"ichinomiya","offset":491}]}